^-|cs||fp||va|4|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|Opener's first responsibility is to clarify whether or not her hand is minimum. With a minimum hand, she rebids 3 of her suit. Note: Minimum or maximum depends on position, vulnerability and suit quality, but in general, 6-8 is minimum and 9-11 is maximum.|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


AT|

With more than a minimum, she shows an outside Feature, normally an ace or king. She is also welcome to find another bid if pressed. With a maximum and no Feature (thus a very good trump suit), bid 3NT. After 2@S-2NT-Opener will make the following bids.|
