^B@2^*BMM:^*N This concludes the article as it appears as a new version in his website. Here, Larry does not fully explain the Feature or Ogust. If interested please study Howard's tutorial on "^*BOgust^*N" at 
|CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/hondoviewer/hondoviewer.php?sf=ogust^*N|CP||AT|. 

BTW, Howard thinks Ogust is better than feature. Ogust lets you describe both the quality of your suit and the strength of your hand. It leads to more accurate bidding when the responder to a weak-2 opener has an invitational hand. However, most players overuse 2NT. It is rare that responder wants to bid 2N. On most hands, responder should either pass or raise based on the number of cards in opener's suit.

Also you can study the "^*BA Comprehensive Review of Weak-2 Opening Bids^*N" by Howard Schutzman at
|CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/hondoviewer/hondoviewer.php?sf=weaktwobids^*N|CP||
